# Wikipedia:Barnstars (Redirect)

## Purpose of This Redirect  
This page exists as a digital courtesy – a polite nod to the chaos that would ensue if every broken link on the internet whined about its abandonment. It redirects users to the current **[Wikipedia:Barnstars](/Wikipedia:Barnstars)** page, where you can read about those shiny virtual badges editors award each other for acts of valor (or more accurately, persistent tinkering with wikitext).  

## Understanding Page Moves  
### Why This Redirect Exists  
When a Wikipedia page undergoes a **[page move](/Page_move)** – essentially digital relocation – this redirect remains like a stubborn ghost haunting the old address. It serves one functional purpose: preventing the digital equivalent of a **[404 error](/HTTP_404)** apocalypse for every internal and external link that once pointed here.  

### Category Affiliation  
This redirect belongs to **[Category:Redirects from moves](/Category:Redirects_from_moves)**, a bureaucratic graveyard where renamed pages linger indefinitely. These redirects are Wikipedia’s version of leaving a forwarding address with the postal service – except here, the mail is perpetually lost if the redirect vanishes.  

